{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/blog/tricking-myself-into-doing-en/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"name":"Shay Yahal","title":"Shay Yahal","description":"Also known as: ShayShu","about":null,"author":"@shayahal1","github":"https://github.com/shayahal","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/shay-yahal/"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"6e01b17c-2b4e-51b4-9c23-34cef9d4db83","excerpt":"Crazy reveal! All the secrets about how I started working out! 💪 Or: why it’s actually not my fault that I forgot to use the task management extension we built…","html":"<p>Crazy reveal! All the secrets about how I started working out! 💪</p>\n<p>Or: why it’s actually not my fault that I forgot to use the task management extension we built.</p>\n<p>So here’s the story - a few weeks ago <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/miki-segall/\">Miki Segall</a> and I built an extension that helps define one important task to complete each day. It was fun, so we sat down last weekend (this time there was no couscous) to do a retro and talk about what’s next.</p>\n<p>In the spirit of “one thing,” let’s start with what bothered me most: I simply forgot to use it. It’s still not a habit.</p>\n<p>This sent me thinking a lot about how I build habits. So despite (or because of) giants having written about this, I decided to share my two cents - in infographic form, of course.</p>\n<p>For me, the challenge with a new habit is actually the negotiation. It’s that moment when my brain, right when needed, starts bargaining with the decision I made. That’s where many habits I tried to establish over the years failed.</p>\n<p>But what did work for me? Building myself a mechanism that neutralizes the negotiation!</p>\n<p>I only work out very early in the morning. There’s no moment when I wonder “Should I work out today?” Instead, the alarm rings, I get organized, and by the time I’ve actually woken up and realized what’s happening - I’m already in the workout.</p>\n<p>An external signal appears, and muscle memory is activated - no time to think! Get up and do it! No negotiations! 🗯️</p>\n<p>And now, the same self-deception technique - also for One Thing.\nAnd the best part - we’re in the chrome store 👏</p>\n<p>Here’s the extension: <a href=\"https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/daily-focus/hfkklmpokpkjifnccffonaigbefileob?hl=en-US&#x26;utm_source=ext_sidebar\">Daily Focus</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; margin: 0 0 30px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/8e1fc/image1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/cbe2e/image1.webp 148w,\n/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/3084c/image1.webp 295w,\n/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/5ca24/image1.webp 590w,\n/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/dad35/image1.webp 885w,\n/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/131f1/image1.webp 900w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/a80bd/image1.jpg 148w,\n/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/1c91a/image1.jpg 295w,\n/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/1c72d/image1.jpg 590w,\n/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/a8a14/image1.jpg 885w,\n/static/54a4e4c8939763a5be1cd41590be26cf/8e1fc/image1.jpg 900w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n            type=\"image/jp